phrases: They said they got a fiefdom,
so I was expecting, well, you know.
This is the middle of nowhere.
I do not mean to be rude,
but I wonder about the previous owner,
letting this place go like that...
The old master died ten years ago
and since he had no heirs,
the land went into the keeping of the queen.
That is why...
The young folks have all given up their land
and gone to the cities.
All you have got left are old-timers like me,
scrabbling along to keep the land tilled.
This region is actually renowned for
its dry land, since it produces great grapes.
Good work, everyone!
Already acting like a feudal lord, I see.
I am not acting!
I really am a feudal lord!
The lord here is Saito, right?
Saito Chevalier De Hiraga...
What else was there?
Saito Chevalier De Hiraga De Ornieres.
That is it!
Still, I was pretty shocked.
I never expected to see you here, Tabitha.
Is it true that you are going to become a queen?
Oh yeah, I wanted to ask about that, too.
What are you going to do?
I have not decided yet.
So what are you doing here?
It is pretty obvious!
Sister wants to hatch an egg!
An egg?
I think she is talking about becoming pregnant
with someone is child.
P-P-Pregnant?
I want to be pregnant, too!
I-I think I should go practice my sword fighting techniques.
Hey, where are you going?
Wait!
I will not be ditched!
I am going too!
The new lords sure are a vigorous bunch.
It would be nice to see a successor born soon.
The Maidens of De Ornieres
It is quite a nice hall for a country mansion.
Those look delicious!
Well, you know what they say.
The way to a man's heart is through his stomach.
Right!
This is more a dump than a basement.
Look at all these books!
Tabitha is going to love this.
I do not think she is really in
the mood for reading right now.
I have never seen her like this.
You are right.
She came here because
she wants to be close to Saito.
She will not have any freedom once she ascends to the throne.
But here she will not be able
to avoid seeing those two together.
Does not that hurt?
That is love.
You know on a rational level,
but you cannot help yourself.
You are right.
This feels so good!
How can you be so laid back about this whole thing?
We have finally got our own house,
but we might as well still be at the academy.
Those are so pretty.
Saito, look!
What is wrong?
Is there something on my face?
No.
Then what is wrong?
Why are you staring at me like that?
I was just thinking about how happy I am.
Seeing you smile makes me happier
than anything else in the world.
Oh, come on.
What are you talking about all of a sudden?
It is the truth.
When I first came here,
I wanted to go back to my world all the time,
but now, I feel like not going back would be okay, too.
It is because you are here.
Saito...
I could not feel like this with another girl.
You are the one who makes me happy.
Saito...
Louise...
I am sorry!
That is not it.
I am just sorry they are so small.
If that was not it, does that mean it is okay?
Can I ask you for a favor?
What is it?
Will you say,
The little meow-meow wants to be teased by the big meow-meow, meow.
Of course that is too much.
Will you be gentle if I say it?
Of course!
Th-The little meow-meow wants to be teased by the big meow-meow, meow.
And can you tell me how?
Well... Um...
You can do what you like, Saito.
Meow!
Lunch is ready, meow.
This idiot made me say it!
Please stop!
Ouch!
I am sorry!
I will never do it again!
That was delicious!
It really was.
Excuse me.
There is someone here to see Miss Louise.
To see me?
Who could it be?
Ow!
Damn you, little Louise!
I have heard all about the indulgent things you have been doing!
Here you go.
Leaving school with a man before getting married,
trying to live in a villa with him...
Do not expect me to ever acknowledge such a filthy relationship!
I do not have to listen to that from
someone who failed to get married.
You would make the House of Valliere
the laughingstock of the country
if the third daughter lived with someone
with a dubious background!
We are going home.
Saito is not dubious!
He is a real nobleman!
He received this land as a reward
from Her Majesty for saving His Holiness!
I do not care, we are leaving!
Please wait!
Elder sister...
You have no business calling me your sister.
Maybe not now.
But I plan on visiting your mother and father
in the near future.
I am going to make Louise happy!
I mean, I will make her happy!
Saito...
There is no way a daughter of Valliere
is going to get married to a
faux-nobleman who cannot even speak properly.
Th-Then...
I will make Saito into a proper nobleman!
If he was a nobleman who you could take to any court,
there would be no problem, right, Eleanor?
You will never take no for an answer.
Fine.
Cram the proper behavior for a nobleman
into his head before I return.
If I am not satisfied, you are coming straight home with me!
Is that understood, Louise?
Perfectly.
Looks like she hates me.
Wh-What was that for?
You mean, Please teach me proper manners
from the ground up.
Go.
We are starting already?
What do you think?
I am going to make you noble, from top to bottom.
Nobody's going to be able to
raise a single complaint against you.
How many times do I have to tell you?
You bow like this.
Now you try.
No, no, no!
May I have the pleasure of this dance?
The way you extend your hand is common.
The way I extend my hand?
Walk slower.
Like this?
You are not a cow!
Moo.
Stop screwing around!
And stop mooing!
Are you really going back?
Yeah.
I was planning on staying over,
but it looks like they are quite busy.
And we did get the grand tour of the place already.
But is not it too late to leave now?
I will take you back.
We might as well take her up on the offer.
Thanks a lot, Tabitha.
Siesta, tell those two we said bye!
No, no, no!
You are doing it all wrong!
You have got absolutely no class!
Start from the beginning.
Did you hear me?
Do it again!
I am done.
What?
I said I am done.
I mean, it is weird that you are trying to change my nature.
But my sister, Eleanor...
Who is going to live with me?
Not your sister, Eleanor.
I do not want anybody to make fun of you!
I do not care if people make fun of me.
But there is no reason we have
to go that far just to live together.
Just do it.
If you want to be with me,
you need to act like a nobleman.
At this rate, I will be taken home.
What are you talking about?
Are you saying your sister's opinion
is more important to you than my feelings?!
I did not say that!
Well, I am not a nobleman!
You are so stubborn!
I could say the same about you!
I cannot sleep in the
same room as someone who is not noble.
Go find yourself another room.
This is my house, and I will sleep where I damn well please!
I probably should not have said those things.
Hey, pal,
what is with these dusty lodgings?
I figured the basement is where I belong,
since I am not a lord and all.
Why do you sound so bitter?
What is all this lord talk, anyway?
Cannot she just be with me because she loves me?
Just the way I am...
Ow.
Is even this chair making a fool of me?!
Huh?
Wow...
Saito?
He is not here either.
Saito?!
Where did he go?
What is this?
Is this some sort of hidden room?
It is a mirror.
I do not remember this hallway.
Sa
What is Her Majesty doing?
Y-Your Majesty?
Saito!
Wh-What is going on?
I am not sure myself.
I opened my closet and then I saw you in the mirror.
The moment I said your name out loud in surprise,
Saito...
I was here.
It looks like there is some kind of spell cast on this mirror
and the mirror in my room.
H-How about first we find you something to wear?
But I really was surprised.
Who would have thought my bedroom
in the castle is connected to this mansion.
I wonder what for.
Looking at how this room is built,
I think it might have been for a mistress.
A mistress?
Yes.
The couple lived upstairs
and the secret trysts were held here.
Trysts...
I would have never imagined that my grandfather had a side like this.
He was regarded as a very strict king.
I suppose he had little choice in who he had to marry.
I was also told by my mother that I should marry.
Countless times.
Marriage...
I have already given up on ever marrying someone I love.
Still, when it comes down to it,
it is hard to convince my heart.
Marrying for my country...
I am sorry.
I do not know what to say in a situation like this...
So you will not tell me that I should not get married.
Of course not.
You are in love with Louise.
I do not know...
Well, if you do not want to, then you should not.
It is weird to marry someone you do not like.
Are you saying that out of pity?
Or...
Even if it is only once in a while,
if you would meet with me like this...
Do not you feel the same way?
So that is what is going on.
Then let us meet here again.
But I... I have Louise.
I understand that.
But the other me keeps saying
that does not matter.
I feel like I have been dreaming.
What is up, pal?
Did you fight with your girl again?
What do you mean?
Wait, was Louise down here?
Yup.
Then she ran out with red eyes.
Could she have...
Louise!
About the princess...
That was just...
I am happy for you that she feels the same way.
Until now, I always thought
I knew everything about you.
I guess I was wrong.
But that is not what happened!
I am sorry.
I am sorry I did not notice until now.
Louise...
Do not give her too much trouble.
Louise!
Should not you go after her?
I do not have the right to do that.
It is better this way.
It is...
Is not the weather today just beautiful, Miss Valliere?
She is gone!
Maybe she ran away with Saito!
I am sorry we kept you here.
But, by the same token, we were actually able to talk.
Give it your best
so that you will not regret anything.
Louise?
What are you doing here, dressed like that?
Did you and Saito already have a marital spat?
We did not have a spat.
I broke up with him.
I mean, I cannot compete against the queen.
It turns out I do not have many places
to go at times like these.
How did it end up like this,
Saito?
I need to talk to you.
About what?
Are you serious about leaving Saito?
It is none of your business.
Then I will take him.
What?
I am the future queen of Gallia,
so I can have whatever I want.
Whatever?
You mean you would force him to...
Are you serious, Tabitha?
And if I am?
Tabitha, what are you talking about?
I could marry him, too, if that was my wish.
M-Marry?!
I will make him happy.
Tabitha, wai
What was that all about?
Kirche?
Do you know why Tabitha said that?
Tabitha understands Queen Henrietta's feelings.
They are one and the same.
They are?
You are not free to love
when you have got a kingdom on your shoulders.
That makes them that much more scary when they are serious.
They will throw all their pride away and go for it,
even if it might not make Saito happy,
or if it meant turning friends into foes...
If someone would go
that far for you, I guess even Saito cannot complain.
Are you ready for that, Louise?
I was thinking that if Saito really did love the queen,
I ought to respect that.
Well, if that is all it takes for you to back off,
then that is how serious your feelings were.
That is not true!
To me, Saito is...
Saito is...
Winning at love is
about being honest with yourself.
Or so I like to think.
I want to go back to my old world.
If I cannot be with Louise,
there is no reason for me to be here.
Saito!
Louise!
What are you doing here?
You are the only one for me, after all.
But I...
I do not care how the queen feels about you.
I want to be with you.
You mean, you forgive me?
Just this once, you hear?
That is the face I love seeing.
That is right.
I am the only one who can make you happy.
Louise...
Saito...
What is this room, anyway?
It is haunted, so I am exorcising it!
Nail!
Yes, madam!
It is your fault for not holding it down properly!
Hey, Saito, what is a hot spring?
What, a place where you feel very good?
And being naked there is the proper behavior?
Next time: Trouble at the Outdoor Bath.
You cannot be naked with anybody else!
Trouble at the Outdoor Bath
